- NVDA niet langer incorrectly reports or locates certain edit velden in MSHTML documenten (e.g. Internet Explorer), specifically where een explicit ARIA role has been used by de web page author. (#2435)
- De backspace key is nu handled correctly when speaking typed words in Windows command consoles. (#2586)
- Cell coordinates in Microsoft Excel are nu shown again in Braille.
- In Microsoft Word, NVDA niet langer leaves you stuck on een paragraph with list formatting when trying to navigate out over een bullet or number with left arrow or control + left arrow. (#2402)
- In browse mode in Mozilla applicaties, de items in certain list boxes (specifically, ARIA list boxes) are niet langer incorrectly rendered.
- In browse mode in Mozilla applicaties, certain controls that were rendered with een incorrect label or just whitespace are nu rendered with de correct label.
- In browse mode in Mozilla applicaties, some extraneous whitespace has been eliminated.
- In browse mode in web browsers, certain graphics that are explicitly marked as presentatieal (specifically, with een alt="" attribute) are nu correctly ignored.
- In web browsers, NVDA nu hides content which is marked as hidden from scherm readers (specifically, using de aria-hidden attribute). (#2117)
- Negative currency amounts (e.g. -$123) are nu correctly spoken as negative, regardless of symbol level. (#2625)
- During say all, NVDA will niet langer incorrectly revert to de default language where een line does not end een sentence. (#2630)
- Font informatie is nu correctly detected in Adobe Reader 10.1 en later. (#2175)
- In Adobe Reader, if alternate text is provided, only that text will be rendered. Previously, extraneous text was sometimes included. (#2174)
- Where een document contains een applicatie, de content of de applicatie is niet langer included in browse mode. This prevents unexpectedly moving inside de applicatie when navigating. You can interact with de applicatie in de same way as voor embedded objects. (#990)
- In Mozilla applicaties, de value of spin knoppen is nu correctly reported when it changes. (#2653)
- Updated support voor Adobe Digital Editions so that it works in version 2.0. (#2688)
- Pressing NVDA+upArrow while on een combo box in Internet Explorer en other MSHTML documenten will niet langer incorrectly read all items. Rather, just de active item will be read. (#2337)
- Speech dictionaries will nu properly save when using een number (#) sign within de pattern or replacement velden. (#961)
