- For de convenience of third party developers, app modules as well as global plugins can nu be reloaded without restarting NVDA. Use tools -> Reload plugins in de NVDA menu or NVDA+control+f3. (#544)
- NVDA nu remembers de position you were at when returning to een previously visited web page. This applies until either de browser or NVDA is exited. (#132)
- Handy Tech brailleleesregels can nu be used without installing de Handy Tech universal driver. (#854)
- Ondersteuning voor several Baum, HumanWare en APH brailleleesregels. (#937)
- De status bar in Media Player Classic Home Cinema is nu recognised.
- De Freedom Scientific Focus 40 Blue brailleleesregel can nu be used when connected via bluetooth. (#1345)


== Veranderingen ==
- Position informatie is niet langer reported by default in some cases where it was usually incorrect; e.g. most menus, de Running Applicaties bar, de Notificatie Area, etc. However, this can be turned on again by een added option in de Object Presentatie settings dialog.
- Keyboard help has been renamed to input help to reflect that it handles input from sources other than de toetsenbord.
- Input Help niet langer reports een script's code locatie via speech en braille as it is cryptic en irrelevant to de user. However, it is nu logged voor developers en advanced users.
- When NVDA detects that it has frozen, it continues to intercept NVDA modifier keys, even though it passes all other keys through to de system. This prevents de user from unintentionally toggling caps lock, etc. if they press een NVDA modifier key without realising NVDA has frozen. (#939)
- If keys are held down after using de pass next key through command, all keys (including key repeats) are nu passed through until de last key is released.
- If een NVDA modifier key is pressed twice in quick succession to pass it through en de second press is held down, all key repeats will nu be passed through as well.
- De volume up, down en mute keys are nu reported in input help. This could be helpful if de user is uncertain as to what these keys are.
- De hotkey voor de Review Cursor item in de NVDA Preferences menu has been changed from r to c to eliminate de conflict with de Braille Settings item.


== Opgeloste Problemen ==
- When adding een nieuw speech dictionary entry, de title of de dialog is nu "Add dictionary entry" instead of "Edit dictionary entry". (#924)
- In speech dictionary dialogs, de content of de Regular expression en Case sensitive kolommen of de Dictionary entries list is nu presented in de configured NVDA language instead of always in English.
- In AIM, position informatie is nu announced in tree views.
- On sliders in de Voice Settings dialog, up arrow/page up/home nu increase de setting en down arrow/page down/end decrease it. Previously, de opposite occurred, which is not logical en is inconsistent with de synth settings ring. (#221)
