- Een virtualBuffer can nu be used to navigate adobe Flash content. Object navigatie en interacting with de controls directly (by turning on focus mode) is still supported. (#453)
- Editable text controls in de Eclipse IDE, including de code editor, are nu accessible. You must be using Eclipse 3.6 or later. (#256, #641)
- NVDA can nu retrieve most text written naar het scherm. (#40, #643)
 - This allows voor reading of controls which do not expose informatie in more direct/reliable ways.
 - Controls made accessible by this feature include: some menu items which display icons (e.g. de Open With menu on files in Windows XP) (#151), editable text velden in Windows Live applicaties (#200), de errors list in Outlook Express (#582), de editable text control in TextPad (#605), lists in Eudora, many controls in Australian E-tax en de formula bar in Microsoft Excel.
- Ondersteuning voor de code editor in Microsoft Visual Studio 2005 en 2008. At least Visual Studio Standard is required; this does not work in de Express editions. (#457)
- Ondersteuning voor IBM Lotus Symphony documenten.
- Early experimental support voor Google Chrome. Please note that Chrome's scherm reader support is far from complete en additional work may also be required in NVDA. You will need een recent development build of Chrome to try this.
