- When switching Windows toetsenbord layouts (with control+shift or alt+shift), de full name of de layout is reported in both speech en braille. Previously it was only reported in speech, en alternative layouts (e.g. Dvorak) were not reported at all.
- If reporting of tabels is disabled, tabel informatie is niet langer announced when de focus changes.
- Certain standard tree view controls in 64 bit applicaties (e.g. de Contents tree view in Microsoft HTML Help) are nu accessible. (#473)
- Fixed some problems with logging of berichten containing non-ASCII karakters. This could cause spurious errors in some cases on non-English systems. (#581)
- De informatie in de About NVDA dialog nu appears in de user's configured language instead of always appearing in English. (#586)
- Problems are niet langer encountered when using de synthesiser settings ring after de voice is changed to one which has less settings than de previous voice.
- In Skype 4.2, contact names are niet langer spoken twice in de contact list.
- Fixed some potentially major memory leaks in de GUI en in virtual buffers. (#590, #591)
- Work around een nasty bug in some SAPI 4 synthesisers which was causing frequent errors en crashes in NVDA. (#597)


= 2009.1 =
Major Hoogtepunten in deze versie include support voor 64 bit editions of Windows; greatly improved support voor Microsoft Internet Explorer en Adobe Reader documenten; support voor Windows 7; reading of de Windows logon, control+alt+delete en User Account Control (UAC) schermen; en de ability to interact with Adobe Flash en Sun Java content on web pages. There have also been several significant stability fixes en verbeteringen to de general user experience.

== Nieuwe Functies ==
- Official support voor 64 bit editions of Windows! (#309)
- Added een synthesizer driver voor de Newfon synthesizer. Note that this requires een special version of Newfon. (#206)
- In virtual buffers, focus mode en browse mode can nu be reported using sounds instead of speech. This is ingeschakeld by default. It can be configured from de Virtual buffers dialog. (#244)
- NVDA niet langer cancels speech when volume control keys are pressed on de toetsenbord, allowing de user to change de volume en listen to actual results immediately. (#287)
- Completely rewritten support voor Microsoft Internet Explorer en Adobe Reader documenten. This support has been unified with de core support used voor Mozilla Gecko, so features such as fast page rendering, extensive quick navigatie, links list, text selection, auto focus mode en braille support are nu available with these documenten.
- Improved support voor de date selection control found in de Windows Vista Date / Time properties dialog.
- improved support voor de Modern XP/Vista start menu (specifically de all programs, en places menus). Appropriate level informatie is nu announced.
- De amount of text that is announced when moving de mouse is nu configurable from de Mouse settings dialog. Een choice of paragraph, line, word or karakter can be made.
- announce spelling errors under de cursor in Microsoft Word.
- support voor de Microsoft Word 2007 spell checker. Partial support may be available voor prior Microsoft Word versions.
- Better support voor Windows Live Mail. Plain text berichten can nu be read en both de plain text en HTML bericht composers are useable.
- In Windows Vista, if de user moves to de secure desktop (either because een UAC control dialog appeared, or because control+alt+delete was pressed), NVDA will announce de fact that de user is nu on de secure desktop.
- NVDA can announce text under de mouse within dos console windows.
- Ondersteuning voor UI Automatie via de UI Automatie client API available in Windows 7, as well as fixes to improve de experience of NVDA in Windows 7.
- NVDA can be configured to start automatisch after you log on to Windows. De option is in de General Settings dialog.
- NVDA can read secure Windows schermen such as de Windows logon, control+alt+delete en User Account Control (UAC) schermen in Windows XP en hoger. Reading of de Windows logon scherm can be configured from de General Settings dialog. (#97)
- Added een driver voor de Optelec ALVA BC6 series brailleleesregels.
- When browsing web documenten, you can nu press n en shift+n to skip forward en backward past blocks of links, respectively.
- When browsing web documenten, ARIA landmarks are nu reported, en you can move forward en backward through them using d en shift+d, respectively. (#192)
- De Links List dialog available when browsing web documenten has nu become een Elements List dialog which can list links, headings en landmarks. Headings en landmarks are presented hierarchically. (#363)
- De nieuw Elements List dialog contains een "Filter by" veld which allows you to filter de list to contain only those items including de text that was typed. (#173)
- Portable versions of NVDA nu look in de 'userConfig' directory inside de NVDA directory, voor de user's configuratie. Like voor de installer version, this keeps de user's configuratie separate from NVDA itself.
- Custom app modules, brailleleesregel drivers en synth drivers can nu be stored in de user's configuratie  directory. (#337)
- Virtual buffers are nu rendered in de background, allowing de user to interact with de system to some extent during de rendering process. De user will be notified that de document is being rendered if it takes longer than een second.
- If NVDA detects that it has frozen voor some reason, it will automatisch pass all keystrokes through so that de user has een better chance of recovering de system.
- Ondersteuning voor ARIA drag en drop in Mozilla Gecko. (#239)
- De document title en current line or selection is nu spoken when you move focus inside een virtual buffer. This makes de behaviour when moving focus into virtual buffers consistent with that voor normal document objects. (#210)
- In virtual buffers, you can nu interact with embedded objects (such as Adobe Flash en Sun Java content) by pressing enter on de object. If it is accessible, you can then tab around it like any other applicatie. To return focus to de document, press NVDA+space. (#431)
- In virtual buffers, o en shift+o move to de next en previous embedded object, respectively.
- NVDA can nu fully access applicaties running as administrator in Windows Vista en later. You must install een official release of NVDA voor this to work. This does not work voor portable versions en snapshots. (#397)


== Veranderingen ==
- NVDA niet langer announces "NVDA started" when it starts.
- De startup en exit sounds are nu played using NVDA's configured audio output device instead of de Windows default audio output device. (#164)
- Progress bar reporting has been improved. Most notably you can nu configure NVDA to announce via both speech en beeps at de same time.
- Some generic roles, such as pane, applicatie en frame, are niet langer reported on focus unless de control is unnamed.
- De review copy command (NVDA+f10) copies de text from de start marker up to en including de current review position, rather than excluding de current position. This allows de last karakter of een line to be copied, which was not previously possible. (#430)
