- Removed de report object group names checkBox from de object presentatie settings dialog, reporting of group names nu is handled differently.


= 0.5 =
- NVDA nu has een built-in synthesizer called eSpeak, developed by Jonathan Duddington.It is very responsive en lite-weight, en has support voor many different languages. Sapi synthesizers can still be used, but eSpeak will be used by default.
 - eSpeak does not depend on any special software to be installed, so it can be used with NVDA on any computer, on een USB thumb drive, or anywhere. 
 - For more info on eSpeak, or to find other versions, go to http://espeak.sourceforge.net/.
- Fix bug where de wrong karakter was being announced when pressing delete in Internet Explorer / Outlook Express editable panes.
- Added support voor more edit velden in Skype.
- VirtualBuffers only get loaded when focus is on de window that needs to be loaded. This fixes some problems when de preview pane is turned on in Outlook Express.
- Added commandline arguments to NVDA:
 - -m, --minimal: do not play startup/exit sounds en do not show de interface on startup if set to do so.
 - -q, --quit: quit any other already running instance of NVDA en then exit
 - -s, --stderr-file fileName: specify where NVDA should place uncaught errors en exceptions
 - -d, --debug-file fileName: specify where NVDA should place debug berichten
 - -c, --config-file: specify een alternative configuratie file  
 - -h, -help: show een help bericht listing commandline arguments
- Fixed bug where punctuatie symbols would not be translated to de appropriate language, when using een language other than english, en when speak typed karakters was turned on.
- Added Slovak language files thanks to Peter Vagner 
- Added een Virtual Buffer settings dialog en een Document Formatting settings dialog, from Peter Vagner.
- Added French translatie thanks to Michel Such 
- Added een script to toggle beeping of progress bars on en off (insert+u). Contributed by Peter Vagner.
- Made more berichten in NVDA be translatable voor other languages. This includes script descriptions when in toetsenbord help.
- Added een find dialog to de virtualBuffers (internet Explorer en Firefox). Pressing control+f when on een page brings up een dialog in which you can type some text to find. Pressing enter will then search voor this text en place de virtualBuffer cursor on this line. Pressing f3 will also search voor de next occurance of de text.
- When speak typed karakters is turned on, more karakters should be nu spoken. Technically, nu ascii karakters from 32 to 255 can nu be spoken.
- Renamed some control types voor better readability. Editable text is nu edit, outline is nu tree view en push knop is nu knop.
- When arrowing around list items in een list, or tree view items in een tree view, de control type (list item, tree view item) is niet langer spoken, to speed up navigatie.
- Has Popup (to indicate that een menu has een submenu) is nu spoken as submenu.
- Where some language use control en alt (or altGR) to enter een special karakter, NVDA nu will speak these karakters when speak typed karakters is on.
- Fixed some problems with reviewing static text controls.
- Added Translatie voor Traditional Chinese, thanks to Coscell Kao.
- Re-structured een important part of de NVDA code, which should nu fix many issues with NVDA's user interface (including settings dialogs).
- Added Sapi4 support to NVDA. Currently there are two sapi4 drivers, one based on code contributed by Serotek Corporatie, en one using de ActiveVoice.ActiveVoice com Interface. Both these drivers have issues, see which one works best voor you.
- Nu when trying to run een nieuw copy of NVDA while een older copy is still running will cause de nieuw copy to just exit. Dit lost een groot probleem op waarbij running multiple copies of NVDA makes your system very unusable.
- Renamed de title of de NVDA user interface from NVDA Interface to NVDA. 
- Fixed een bug in Outlook Express where pressing backspace at de start of een editable bericht would cause een error.
- Added patch from Rui Batista that adds een script to report de current battery status on laptops (insert+shift+b).
- Added een synth driver called Silence. This is een synth driver that does not speak anything, allowing NVDA to stay completely silent at all times. Eventually this could be used along with Braille support, when we have it.
- Added capitalPitchChange setting voor synthesizers thanks to J.J. Meddaugh
- Added patch from J.J. Meddaugh that makes de toggle report objects under mouse script more like de other toggle scripts (saying on/off rather than changing de whole statement).
- Added spanish translatie (es) contributed by Juan C. buo.
- Added Hungarian language file from Tamas Gczy.
- Added Portuguese language file from Rui Batista.
- Changing de voice in de voice settings dialog nu sets de rate, pitch en volume sliders to de nieuw values according to de synthesizer, rather than forcing de synthesizer to be set to de old values. This fixes issues where een synth like eloquence or viavoice seems to speek at een much faster rate than all other synths.
- Fixed een bug where either speech would stop, or NVDA would entirely crash, when in een Dos console window.
- If support voor een particular language exists, NVDA nu automatisch can show its interface en speak its berichten in de language Windows is set to. Een particular language can still be chosen manualy from de user interface settings dialog as well.
- Added script 'toggleReportDynamicContentVeranderingen' (insert+5). This toggles whether nieuw text, or other dynamic changes should be automatisch announced. So far this only works in Dos Console Windows.
- Added script 'toggleCaretMovesReviewCursor' (insert+6). This toggles whether de review cursor should be automatisch repositioned when de system caret moves. This is useful in Dos console windows when trying to read informatie as het scherm is updating.
- Added script 'toggleFocusMovesNavigatorObject' (insert+7). This toggles whether de navigator object is repositioned on de object with focus as it changes.
- Added some documentatie translated in to various languages. So far there is French, Spannish en Finish.
- Removed some developer documentatie from de binary distribution of NVDA, it is only nu in de source version.
- Fixed een possible bug in Windows Live Messanger en MSN Messenger where arrowing up en down de contact list would cause errors.
- Nieuw berichten are nu automatisch spoken when in een conversatie using Windows Live Messenger. (only works voor English versions so far)
- De history window in een Windows Live Messenger conversatie can nu be read by using de arrow keys. (Only works voor English versions so far) 
- Added script 'passNextKeyThrough' (insert+f2). Press this key, en then de next key pressed will be passed straight through to Windows. This is useful if you have to press een certain key in een applicatie but NVDA uses that key voor something else.
- NVDA niet langer freezes up voor more than een minute when opening very large documenten in MS Word.
- Fixed een bug where moving out of een tabel in MS Word, en then moving back in, caused de current row/kolom numbers not to be spoken if moving back in to exactly de same cell.
- When starting NVDA with een synthesizer that doesn't exist, or is not working, de sapi5 synth will try en be loaded in stead, or if sapi5 isn't working, then speech will be set to silence.
- Increasing en decreasing rate scripts can niet langer take de rate hoger 100 or below 0.
- If there is een error with een language when choosing it in de User Interface Settings dialog, een bericht box will alert de user to de fact.
- NVDA nu asks if it should save configuratie en restart if de user has just changed de language in de User Interface Settings Dialog. NVDA must be restarted voor de language change to fully take effect.
- If een synthesizer can not be loaded, when choosing it from de synthesizer dialog, een bericht box alerts de user to de fact.
- When loading een synthesizer voor de first time, NVDA lets de synthesizer choose de most suitable voice, rate en pitch parameters, rather than forcing it to defaults it thinks are ok. Dit lost een probleem op where Eloquence en Viavoice sapi4 synths start speaking way too fast voor de first time.

